  "prompt": "What is the meaning of \"i\" in iPhone?",
  "response": "The \"i\" in iPhone originally stood for \"internet.\" When Apple first introduced the iMac in 1998, Steve Jobs explained that the \"i\" in iMac stood for \"internet,\" and also mentioned concepts like \"individual,\" \"instruct,\" \"inform,\" and \"inspire.\" Since then, Apple has used the \"i\" prefix for a number of products, including the iPod, iPhone, and iPad, maintaining a connection to the idea of the internet and personal empowerment.",
